    <text>
        <body>
            <p>May <del>?</del> God grant his holy blessing on the eve of his holy
                    <date>Sabbath</date> to him<lb/> who occupies himself in His holy work, by
                spreading new light, that is<lb/> my friend and my dear, the wise and the talented,
                our teacher, <persName><sic>UriLippman</sic><lb/> Leeser</persName>.</p>
            <p>Dear friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In spite of great stress, I am continuing to send you the<lb/>
                promised work. You will, no doubt, find your way through the dark forest.<lb/> On
                    <date>Monday</date>, you will receive the end five sheets. Now, please note:</p>
            <p>1. That, wherever possible, you begin your translation at the same time.<lb/> Should
                this be impossible, then the translation, which you will announce<lb/> at the same
                time, must follow in the <date>January</date> issue. In any event, the<lb/> German
                text must be in the <date>December</date> issue, along with that which I am<lb/>
                still to send you.</p>
            <p>2. Please see to it yourself that there are no mistakes in it.</p>
            <p>3. I have myself marked the sheets with numbers. Please observe this.</p>
            <p>4. Note what must be added at the end of page three and that which is marked<lb/>
                with the number 4. It belongs to the text. Here I must ask you again<lb/> to be
                exact, since that which belongs to, “Developing Legends is writ-<lb/>en above, and
                then there follows the statement, “Were and are frequent-<lb/>ly history”,
                conclusion against <persName>Wise</persName> and his cronies.</p>
            <p>5. The note, “<persName>Ewald</persName>, etc.” you will put in the proper place
                until “Of all <lb/> nations”.</p>
            <p>6. In any event, I must have the proof sheets.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I think that I have properly disposed of <persName>Jost</persName>,
                and have char-<lb/>acterized his entire point of view from the beginning.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I ask for a quick response.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Your friend and admirer,</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Please attend to the matter of the express charges in the near future.</p>
        </body>
